\title{Principal judgement}

\p{The \em{principal judgement} of a rule is the judgement containing the [principle
connective](type-systems-000R).} 

\ul{

\li{In an [introduction rule](type-systems-000J), the principle judgement is usually the
conclusion.}

\li{In an [elimination rule](type-systems-000K), the principle judgement is usually the
first premise.}}
